      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ROCK 'N' THE JAM (5) continued his rise through the ranks with an impressive win from the front over 1800m last time out to go back-to-back. Tougher again here, but he's a very nice horse on the rise. Can be handy in the run and put his rivals to the sword once again. FANCY RED (2) finished off strongly from back in the pack over 1800m last time out and steps up in trip again today. She wasn't beaten far in the Bunbury Cup where she jumped favourite over this trip three back. Should be up front for CJP and be in this for a long way. ROYAL LAW (1) bolted in by 3.8L in the Geraldton Cup, stamping his authority in the win. The inside draw should see him well placed in the run and Faithfull remains in the saddle. Can repeat the dose without surprising. ROCKING SOCIETY (3) gets a weight swing in his favour off the Geraldton Cup and is not to be discounted. RIVER RUBICON (4) is next best off a better performance last start.",
